title: Sacred Monkey Forest Sanctuary
address: Jl. Monkey Forest, Ubud, Kecamatan Ubud, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80571
note_from_owner:
The Monkey Forest in Ubud is a lush, enchanting sanctuary nestled in the heart of Bali. Officially known as the Sacred Monkey Forest Sanctuary, this sprawling reserve is home to hundreds of playful long-tailed macaques.
It serves not only as a wildlife haven but also as a site of spiritual and cultural significance, with ancient temples and sacred groves scattered throughout the forest.
Managed by the Management of Monkey Forest and Padangtegal village, the Monkey Forest is both a popular tourist destination and a vital center for conservation and local heritage, offering visitors a unique blend of natural beauty and cultural depth.

title: Objek Wisata Sangeh
address: Jl. Brahmana, Sangeh, Kec. Abiansemal, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80352
note_from_owner:
Obyek wisata kera dengan hutan palanya yang sudah berusia ratusan tahun. Obyek wisata ini dirintis pada tgl 1 Januari 1969.
Jenis-jenis satwa yang paling dominan dan mejadi ciri khas kawasan ini adalah kera abu-abu (Macaca faciculari) dimana populasinya berdasarkan inventarisasi tahun 1993 sebanyak 22 jenis antara lain : Alap-alap (Elanus hypoleucu), Elang (Halioaster Indus), Burung Hantu (Typte alba javanica), Terocok (Gouvier ahalis), Musang (Paradorurus hermaproditus), Kucing hutan (Felis bengalensis), Sendanglawe (Ciconia episcepus) dan lain sebagainya.
Sarana Wisata Alam

Hutan Pala Sangeh dihuni oleh kera abu ekor panjang (Macaca fascicularis) yang jumlahnya saat ini kurang lebih 600 ekor.

title: Temesi Waterfall
address: Jalan Subak Pengliklikan, Temesi, Gianyar, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80515
note_from_owner: This waterfall falls from a steep cliff and is surrounded by dense forest, so it is no less beautiful if you just want to admire it from a distance. The shallow natural pool located in the river is perfect for playing in the water and soaking for hours while enjoying the peaceful natural atmosphere, and the best part is that the location is not far from Ubud, about 30 minutes and only takes 7 minutes on foot from the parking area. Temesi Waterfall is also a suitable place for freewed photos, because there are many charming photo spots here, and for those who want to take freewed photos, please make a reservation in advance and for freewed photos it will be open from 06.00 to 08.30 only.

Informasi Penting Mengenai Melukat di Tempat Kami

* Tidak perlu reservasi.
* Bisa melakukan melukat secara mandiri.

Ketentuan untuk Non-Hindu:
* Reservasi wajib.

title: Setia Darma House of Mask and Puppets
address: Jalan Tegal Bingin, Banjar Tengkulak Tengah, Kemenuh, Sukawati, Gianyar Regency, Bali 80582
street: Jalan Tegal Bingin, Banjar Tengkulak Tengah
note_from_owner:
The House of Masks and Puppets was initiated by Mr. Hadi Sunyoto, a businessman and cultural enthusiast assisted by the late Mr. Agustinus Prayitno, a lover of antiques and culture. Both of them has been collecting masks and puppets from different regions in Indonesia for the past years. Mr. Hadi decided to create a space to collect, preserve and spread the knowledge of the art form of masks and puppets. As a result, the House of Masks and Puppets was open 2006.
The use of the word house for the space is used to signify the space as a place for activities, just like a house is.

title: Kecak & Fire Dance at Tanah Gajah, Ubud
address: Tanah Gajah, a Resort by Hadiprana, Jl. Raya Goa Gajah, Tengkulak Kaja, Kecamatan Ubud, Bali 80571
street: Tanah Gajah, a Resort by Hadiprana, Jl. Raya Goa Gajah
note_from_owner:
PERFORMED EVERY TUESDAY & FRIDAY EVENING AT 19:00
*Also performing every Sunday evening at 19:00 until 3 September 2023*

Ubud is the cultural centre of Bali and is famous for its dances, and Tanah Gajah Ubud is proud to host a dance troupe of between fifty and seventy boys and men from the local community who perform the Kecak dance.

The spectacular 30 minute-long Balinese Kecak and fire dance performances are held at Tanah Gajah Ubud's candle-lit outdoor amphitheatre, , followed by an opportunity for guests to take photos with the talented performers before heading to The Tempayan restaurant for the Royal Rijsttafel dinner experience.

Taman Nusa is an Indonesian Cultural Park that aims to offer a comprehensive and interactive experience on the cultures of Indonesia's many ethnic groups, set againts the natural backdrop of Bali.
Situated on 10 hectares of land, visitors will feel as if they have travelled around Indonesia - with more than 60 traditional houses and some that are hundreds of years old.
